      },
      "date": "2012-08-15 19:00:33.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nThis leaves the code in a very obviously broken state if you change the header file name, but don't update all of the places that use that file.\n\nIts not clear to me either what the removal of the LASSERTs has to do with renaming liblustreapi.h.  I think that belongs in a separate patch.\n\nI'd really suggest that we go back to my original patch.  I think that the only serious complaint there was that there was further work that needed to be done.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "017c626ab9601aa592c6c55900db8cecd9428919",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 109,
        "name": "Christopher J. Morrone",
        "email": "morrone2@llnl.gov",
        "username": "morrone"
      },
      "date": "2012-08-15 19:17:58.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nOh actually, the backwards-compatibility part should allow the old header file name to continue to work.  But I still think that this commit is the reasonable place to update all of the header file includes to use the new name.  That makes this one self-contained commit that does one clear logical change: rename the header file.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
